Image 10, 2013＿9_image_6.jpg: This image is excellent because it captures an extraordinary natural phenomenon known as the halo effect, which is a unique optical illusion that occurs when light passes through a cloud or fog layer. The halo effect results from the refraction, reflection, and dispersion of light in the atmosphere, creating a circular, multicolored ring surrounding the object in the scene. The presence of a mountain range and a cloudy sky creates an ideal setting for the appearance of the halo effect. It is not an excellent image because of the lack of focus in certain details, making it difficult to fully appreciate the beauty and the phenomenon of the halo effect. The halo appears to be a more abstract and less defined image, compared to other beautiful photographs that showcase the natural beauty of a mountain and the surrounding atmosphere.

The image is not excellent because it is a black and white image and does not capture the full range of colors that can be expected in the aurora. The lack of color could be a limitation of the photograph, making it difficult to fully appreciate the beauty and vibrancy of these natural phenomena.
